# README #

This README would normally document whatever steps are necessary to get your application up and running.

### How do I get set up? ###

* First, we need our most important requirement Node.JS (To install, simply visit http://nodejs.org/)
* Open up your command-line interface (Terminal for OSX/Ubuntu, Command Prompt, Git Bash, Node.JS command prompt for Windows)
* Clone the project, in your command-line application type : "git clone ..."
* To navigate to our project folder, in your command-line application type : "cd path-to/socle-gulp"
* To install scss lint : "gem install scss_lint"
--> If (ERROR:  Could not find a valid gem 'scss_lint' (>= 0), here is why:Unable to download data from https://rubygems.org/ - SSL_connect returned=1 errno=0 state=SSLv3 read server certificate B: certificate verify failed (https://api.rubygems.org/specs.4.8.gz)) : "gem install scss_lint --source http://api.rubygems.org"
* To install scss lint reporter checkstyle : "gem install scss_lint_reporter_checkstyle"
--> If (ERROR:  Could not find a valid gem 'scss_lint_reporter_checkstyle' (>= 0), here is why:Unable to download data from https://rubygems.org/ - SSL_connect returned=1 errno=0 state=SSLv3 read server certificate B: certificate verify failed (https://api.rubygems.org/specs.4.8.gz)) : "gem install scss_lint_reporter_checkstyle --source http://api.rubygems.org"
* To install Required Plugins, in your command-line application type : "npm install"
* To run Gulp, in your command-line application type : "gulp" && "gulp watch"

